(43, 12, 26, 51, 3, 24, 24, 'serve me', 'Service and Reward Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of serving Christ and the associated rewards. John 12:26 speaks of being honored by the Father for service, while Colossians 3:24 highlights receiving a reward from the Lord for serving Him.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 26, 9, 2, 30, 30, 'him will my Father honour', 'Connection of Honor and Service', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of honor linked to service and obedience. In John 12:26, serving Jesus leads to being honored by the Father, while 1 Samuel 2:30 states that those who honor God will be honored in return.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 26, 48, 1, 10, 10, NULL, 'Servanthood in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being a servant of Christ. John 12:26 highlights the honor given to those who serve Jesus, while Galatians 1:10 contrasts pleasing men with being a servant of Christ.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 26, 43, 10, 27, 27, 'let him follow me', 'Following the Shepherd', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of following Jesus. In John 12:26, serving Jesus involves following Him, while John 10:27 highlights that His sheep hear His voice and follow Him.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 26, 43, 17, 24, 24, 'where I am', 'Servanthood and Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being with Jesus. John 12:26 states that servants will be where He is, while John 17:24 expresses Jesus'' desire for His followers to be with Him. This connection highlights the importance of proximity to Christ for those who serve Him.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 26, 45, 1, 1, 1, 'serve me', 'Servanthood and Following Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of servanthood to Jesus. John 12:26 speaks of serving and following Christ, while Romans 1:1 identifies Paul as a servant of Jesus Christ, highlighting the call to serve in the gospel.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 26, 19, 91, 15, 15, NULL, 'Service and Divine Honor', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of service and the resulting honor from God. In John 12:26, serving Christ leads to being honored by the Father, while Psalms 91:15 promises deliverance and honor for those who call upon God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 27, 43, 12, 23, 23, 'this hour', 'Connection of Jesus'' Hour', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of ''this hour'' in relation to Jesus'' mission. The first passage reveals Jesus'' troubled soul as he approaches this pivotal moment, while the second announces the arrival of that hour for his glorification.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 27, 58, 5, 7, 7, 'my soul troubled', 'Connection of Suffering and Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of deep emotional turmoil and the act of prayer in the face of impending death. John 12:27 speaks of a troubled soul, while Hebrews 5:7 describes prayers offered with strong crying and tears.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
