(43, 12, 27, 40, 26, 42, 42, 'this hour', 'Connection of Jesus'' Troubled Soul', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' emotional turmoil as he faces his impending suffering. The phrase ''thy will be done'' in Matthew reflects his acceptance of the hour he refers to in John.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 27, 43, 13, 21, 21, 'my soul troubled', 'Connection of Troubled Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' troubled state. In John 12:27, he expresses his inner turmoil about his impending fate, while in John 13:21, he is again described as troubled in spirit due to betrayal.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 27, 19, 69, 1, 3, 'my soul troubled', 'Connection of Distress and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize a deep sense of trouble and a plea for salvation. John 12:27''s ''my soul troubled'' resonates with Psalms 69:1''s ''the waters are come in unto my soul,'' highlighting a shared theme of distress.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 27, 19, 88, 3, 3, 'my soul troubled', 'Connection of Troubled Souls', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of a troubled soul facing deep distress. John 12:27 reflects Jesus'' turmoil as he approaches his purpose, while Psalms 88:3 expresses a similar anguish of life nearing its end.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 28, 43, 13, 31, 32, 'glorified', 'Glorification of God and Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorification, with John 12:28 stating, ''I have both glorified it,'' and John 13:31 declaring, ''Now is the Son of man glorified.'' This connection highlights the continuity of God''s glory being revealed through Jesus.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 28, 40, 26, 42, 42, NULL, 'Divine Will and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize submission to God''s will. In John, the glorification of God''s name is central, while in Matthew, the plea for God''s will to be done reflects a similar theme of obedience.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 28, 66, 5, 9, 14, 'glorify thy name', 'Glorification of the Lamb', 'Both passages emphasize the glorification of God and the Lamb. John 12:28 speaks of God''s name being glorified, while Revelation 5:12 declares the Lamb''s worthiness to receive glory and honor.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 28, 43, 11, 40, 44, NULL, 'Glory of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorifying God. In John 12:28, Jesus calls for God''s name to be glorified, while in John 11:40, He indicates that belief will reveal the glory of God through the miracle of Lazarus''s resurrection.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 28, 23, 49, 3, 7, 'glorified it, and will glorify it again', 'Glorification of God''s Servant', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorification associated with God''s servant. In John 12:28, the voice from heaven affirms the glorification of God''s name, while Isaiah 49:3 speaks of God''s servant, Israel, in whom He will be glorified.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 28, 40, 3, 17, 17, 'glorify thy name', 'Divine Affirmation of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the divine voice affirming Jesus'' identity and mission. Both passages feature a voice from heaven that emphasizes God''s approval and glory associated with Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 28, 50, 1, 6, 11, 'glorify thy name', 'Glorification of God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorifying God. In John 12:28, the voice from heaven affirms God''s glory, while Philippians 1:11 speaks of being filled with the fruits of righteousness unto the glory and praise of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
