(43, 12, 29, 66, 6, 1, 1, 'it thundered', 'Thunder as Divine Communication', 'This connection highlights the motif of thunder as a form of divine communication. In both passages, the presence of thunder signifies a significant moment of revelation or response from God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 29, 66, 14, 2, 2, NULL, 'Voice and Thunder Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the powerful nature of divine communication, with John noting the voice perceived as thunder and Revelation describing a voice as ''the voice of great thunder.'' This connection highlights the awe-inspiring presence of God''s voice.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
